description:
Huss and Jerome: After John Wycliffes reform ideas shook England, they spread to continental Europe and were picked up by Huss and Jerome in Prague. Here these two young men led a reform in Bohemia that made a lasting impact, but each would sadly lose their lives in the most gruesome way possible.
